<TITLE> Dr Taslim to sit on central bank board </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 29 (bdnews24.com)  Professor Mohammad Ali Taslim of Dhaka University has been appointed to the board of the Bangladesh Bank, an official said. AFM Asaduzzaman, an aide to the governor, told bdnews24.com that the central bank had received the government order Tuesday afternoon. Dr Taslim, a former chairman of Bangladesh Tariff Commission, replaces Hossain Zillur Rahman who had been appointed adviser to the caretaker government. Taslim, who teaches Economics at DU, is a member of the Bangladesh Better Business Forum and co-chairs its macro-economic policy committee. bdn
